# Write Tests

Write tests for a module in **{{PROJECT_NAME}}** using **{{TEST_RUNNER}}**.

## Steps

1. Read `.github/copilot-instructions.md` for project-wide conventions
2. Read the module to be tested — understand its public interface and behavior
3. Survey existing tests in `{{TESTS_PATH}}` to understand test patterns and helpers
4. Write tests covering:
   - Happy path (expected inputs, expected outputs)
   - Edge cases (empty, null, boundary values)
   - Error paths (invalid inputs, failure conditions)
5. Run `{{TEST_RUNNER}}` — all tests must pass
6. Report coverage improvement (before vs after if measurable)

## Testing principles

- Test behavior, not implementation
- Each test has one clear assertion or related group
- Test names describe the scenario: `"should return 404 when user not found"`
- Mock only at system boundaries: network calls, database, file I/O, time

